million from
real estate and other business
failures.

02:21.241 --> 02:26.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That could have legally allowed
him to avoid
paying income taxes for 18
years.

02:26.980 --> 02:30.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Clinton campaign quickly
produced a TV
ad on the issue.

02:30.317 --> 02:35.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: A new report shows he
may not have
paid any federal taxes for
almost 20 years.

02:35.422 --> 02:37.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON: He
didn't pay any
federal income tax.

02:37.958 --> 02:39.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
That makes me smart.

02:39.626 --> 02:43.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NARRATOR: If he thinks that
makes him smart,
what does he think of you?

02:43.563 --> 02:47.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Late today at a rally
in Colorado,
Trump fired back.

02:47.801 --> 02:52.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: As a businessman
and real estate
developer, I have legally used
the tax laws

02:52.939 --> 03:00.847 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to my benefit and to the benefit
of my company,
my investors and my employees.

03:00.881 --> 03:02.649 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

03:02.682 --> 03:07.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I mean, honestly,
I have brilliantly
-- I have brilliantly used those
laws.

03:07.854 --> 03:13.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have often said, on the
campaign trail,
that I have a fiduciary
responsibility to

03:13.593 --> 03:21.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pay no more tax than is legally
required,
like anybody else, or, to put it
another way,

03:21.268 --> 03:26.339 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to pay as little tax as legally
possible.

03:26.373 --> 03:32.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The Republican
nominee is under
fire on several other fronts,
including allegation

03:32.212 --> 03:37.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he routinely demeaned women
on his reality
TV show "The Apprentice."

03:37.284 --> 03:43.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
