this year's Nobel
Prize in medicine.

08:06.786 --> 08:12.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yoshinori Ohsumi was honored
today for discoveries
on how cells break down and
recycle.

08:12.625 --> 08:18.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His work in the 1990s may now
aid research
on fighting cancer, Alzheimer's
and other

08:18.565 --> 08:20.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
diseases.

08:20.367 --> 08:25.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Japan today, Ohsumi said he
never imagined
that his experiments with yeast
would mean

08:25.105 --> 08:26.906 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a Nobel.

08:26.940 --> 08:30.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YOSHINORI OHSUMI, Nobel Prize
Winner (through
translator): There is one thing
I would like

08:30.043 --> 08:31.978 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to stress.

08:32.011 --> 08:35.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I began this research,
there was no assurance
whatsoever that it would lead to
some connection

08:35.181 --> 08:37.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with cancer or human longevity.

08:37.384 --> 08:39.252 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's not why I started.

08:39.285 --> 08:42.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Such is the nature of how
fundamental research
unfolds, and I stress the
importance of the

08:42.989 --> 08:44.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
fundamentals of science.

08:44.791 --> 08:50.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Along with a
Nobel medal, Ohsumi
receives prize money worth
$930,000.

08:50.497 --> 08:58.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
