WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But yes-voters
complained
opponents of the peace deal were
misguided.

10:22.956 --> 10:26.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANTONIO SANGUINO, Colombia
(through translator):
Fifty percent of the people who
went out to

10:26.893 --> 10:31.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
vote allowed themselves to be
convinced by
a message of hate, a message of
revenge, a

10:31.764 --> 10:33.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
message of keeping us in the
past.

10:33.566 --> 10:37.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The government
and the leftist
rebels signed the peace pact one
week ago

10:37.170 --> 10:39.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
