25:35.501 --> 25:42.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS set fire to Qayyarah oil
wells in retreat.

25:42.341 --> 25:47.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This road is the front line
before getting
to ISIS-controlled Mosul, and
all along the

25:47.880 --> 25:53.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
front line here, it is divided
up between
the various groups who are
fighting ISIS.

25:53.485 --> 25:58.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It represents just how complex
the battle
for Mosul will be.

25:58.257 --> 26:06.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. Major General Gary Volesky,
commander
of the Army's 101st Airborne
Division, knows

26:06.532 --> 26:11.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the difficulties involved in
getting Iraq's
combative factions to work
together.

26:11.103 --> 26:16.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"PBS NewsHour" traveled with the
general to
Qayyarah Air Field, destroyed by
ISIS as they

26:16.442 --> 26:19.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
left here, he says.

26:19.845 --> 26:25.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This will be the major hub,
where U.S. support
troops and Iraqi forces will
work together

26:25.117 --> 26:26.618 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as the offensive gets under way.

26:26.652 --> 26:27.619 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
MAJ.

26:27.653 --> 26:29.321 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

26:29.354 --> 26:31.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GARY VOLESKY, U.S. Army: All of
the stakeholders
recognize the importance of
Mosul.

26:31.156 --> 26:34.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, we have been to meetings
with both
the Kurds, the Iraqis, a lot of
the different

26:34.560 --> 26:40.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stakeholders, if you will, and
they all understand
that they have got to come
together to defeat

26:40.566 --> 26:41.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Da'esh.

26:41.567 --> 26:43.335 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's what they are doing.

26:43.368 --> 26:47.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: In 2003, during
the early days
of the American occupation here,
the 101st

26:47.339 --> 26:50.209 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Airborne was responsible for
Mosul.

26:50.242 --> 26:53.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Colonel Brett Sylvia knows that
role has now
changed.

26:53.912 --> 26:54.880 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

26:54.913 --> 26:56.682 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRETT SYLVIA, U.S. Army: I am a
soldier.

26:56.715 --> 27:01.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there is no doubt that if
you ask me where
I wanted to be, it would be up
front, you

27:01.520 --> 27:04.223 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know, with a rifle in my hand
leading.

27:04.256 --> 27:06.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But that's not our role today.

27:07.025 --> 27:10.462 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our role is to advise and assist
them.

27:10.496 --> 27:13.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, to be honest with you, it
may very well
be the right strategy.

27:13.365 --> 27:20.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: U.S. commanders
hope their
latest efforts will prevent
another 13 years

27:20.038 --> 27:21.773 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of bloodshed and fighting.

27:21.807 --> 27:22.875 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

27:22.908 --> 27:25.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRETT SYLVIA: I do have a son in
the military
now.

27:25.944 --> 27:31.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I do think about it a lot,
about, what
I am doing today in order to be
able to create

27:31.416 --> 27:36.989 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a long-lasting stability, such
that he may
not have to come here?

27:37.022 --> 27:43.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Stability of any
kind has eluded
this land for so long that
refugees fleeing

27:43.095 --> 27:46.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mosul will have to survive in
places like
this.

27:46.965 --> 27:51.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As many as a million civilians
live in Mosul
City right now.

27:51.303 --> 27:58.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When they flee, the humanitarian
crisis could
accelerate from grave to
disaster.

27:58.110 --> 28:01.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Camps are already stretched
beyond capacity.

28:01.480 --> 28:06.518 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The United Nations is
frantically trying to
expand this facility to absorb
the expected

28:06.552 --> 28:08.353 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
new arrivals.

28:08.387 --> 28:13.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: It is also going to start
to be raining,
and the winter season is going
to make any

28:13.292 --> 28:17.129 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
