28:33.745 --> 28:39.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: How long they
must stay here
will depend on how the fight for
Mosul plays

28:39.651 --> 28:40.986 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
out.

28:41.019 --> 28:43.889 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Defeating ISIS is a short-term
goal.

28:43.922 --> 28:48.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But once they have been pushed
out of the
city, keeping those who have
fought them from

28:48.393 --> 28:52.064 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
turning on each other will be
the next challenge.

28:52.097 --> 28:58.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their hatred of ISIS is the only
thing that
binds many of Iraq's fighting
forces together.

28:58.971 --> 29:10.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Jane
Ferguson
in Qayyarah, Iraq.

