opinion, this despite
the fact that, if Trump wins, he
would be

36:48.773 --> 36:53.778 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the oldest newly elected
president to take
office, while Clinton would be
the second

36:53.812 --> 36:55.547 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
oldest.

36:55.580 --> 36:58.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Americans will have a chance to
compare the
two running mates when they face
off on the

36:58.616 --> 37:01.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
debate stage tomorrow night in
Virginia.

37:01.886 --> 37:05.757 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We take a look now at how these
two competitors
got to where they are today.

37:05.790 --> 37:07.492 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

37:07.525 --> 37:08.293 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM KAINE (D-VA), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
Are we going to let him get away
with it?

37:08.326 --> 37:09.294 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AUDIENCE: No!

37:09.327 --> 37:10.295 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

37:10.328 --> 37:11.296 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TIM KAINE: Absolutely not.

37:11.329 --> 37:12.964 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We can't.

37:12.997 --> 37:14.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Today, they
represent polar
opposites of the political
spectrum.

37:14.065 --> 37:15.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

37:15.934 --> 37:18.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE PENCE (R-IN), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
I know that I know we will make
America great

37:18.103 --> 37:19.070 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
again.

37:19.104 --> 37:20.905 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

37:20.939 --> 37:24.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But long before
they were vying
to be the nation's second in
command, Mike

37:24.275 --> 37:30.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pence and Tim Kaine began their
path to politics
under strikingly similar
circumstances.

37:30.782 --> 37:37.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Both were sons of the Midwest,
in Pence's
case, Columbus, Indiana, raised
by a gas station

37:37.856 --> 37:41.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
