faith manifests

38:37.849 --> 38:39.684 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
itself in political action.

38:39.717 --> 38:45.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Like Kaine, Pence
was a Catholic
school kid, serving as an altar
boy, sometimes

38:45.423 --> 38:47.058 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
seven days a week.

38:47.091 --> 38:53.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The future GOP governor also had
an early
interest in politics, Democratic
politics,

38:53.198 --> 38:54.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
says Maureen Groppe of The
Indianapolis Star.

38:54.866 --> 38:57.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN GROPPE, The Indianapolis
Star: He
was a youth coordinator for the
Democratic

38:57.802 --> 39:00.872 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Party in his county at one
point.

39:00.905 --> 39:02.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He revered the Kennedys.

39:02.740 --> 39:05.109 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He had a bust of JFK.

39:05.143 --> 39:08.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He voted for Carter, but his
politics started
to change in college.

39:09.013 --> 39:12.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said Ronald Reagan inspired
him to become
a Republican.

39:12.383 --> 39:18.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He thought that Reagan embodied
the ideals
of America that he was raised to
believe in.

39:18.690 --> 39:21.326 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Both men went on
to study law.

39:21.359 --> 39:25.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Kaine took a detour to
Honduras to work
with a Jesuit mission.

39:26.030 --> 39:31.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SCHAPIRO: Then, when he
indicated to
the Jesuits present there that
he was a law

39:31.803 --> 39:37.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
student, he was told that that
was not necessarily
a skill that would be useful in
a Third World

39:37.442 --> 39:39.277 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
country.

39:39.310 --> 39:46.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he spent a year teaching
crafts, metalwork,
carpentry to youngsters at this
missionary.

39:46.618 --> 39:48.386 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

39:48.419 --> 39:50.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM KAINE: And it convinced me
that we have
got to advance opportunity and
equality for

39:50.455 --> 39:54.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
everybody, no matter where they
come from,
how much money they have, what
they look like,

39:54.826 --> 39:57.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what accent they have, or who
they love.

39:57.061 --> 39:58.796 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

39:58.830 --> 40:02.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: After law school,
the newly
wed Kaine settled in Richmond,
Virginia, to

40:03.001 --> 40:07.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be close to his wife's family
and launch his
legal career.

40:07.772 --> 40:12.477 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pence did the same in his home
state, Indiana,
and mulled his next step.

40:12.510 --> 40:15.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN GROPPE: When he was
thinking about
what he wanted to do with his
life, he thought

40:15.480 --> 40:21.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about his gifts, his talents,
and he thought
he had a gift for articulation
for advocacy.

40:21.619 --> 40:24.389 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he wanted to try and use
that in some
way.

40:24.422 --> 40:30.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: After two failed
runs for Congress
in the '80s, that gift led Pence
to start

40:30.395 --> 40:32.196 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
his own radio talk show.

40:32.230 --> 40:33.197 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

40:33.231 --> 40:34.198 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MIKE PENCE: And I'm supposed to
be a cynic.

40:34.232 --> 40:35.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm supposed to not appropriate
you people.

40:35.800 --> 40:38.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAUREEN GROPPE: He said that his
show was
Rush Limbaugh on decaf.

40:39.003 --> 40:42.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he also likes to say that
he's a conservative,
but he's not in a bad mood about
it.

40:42.607 --> 40:48.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also during this
time, Pence
moved away from his Catholic
upbringing, joining

40:48.079 --> 40:51.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an evangelical Christian church
in Indianapolis.

40:51.516 --> 40:55.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In 2000, Pence ran for Congress
again.

40:55.219 --> 40:57.088 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The third time was the charm.

40:57.121 --> 41:02.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He quickly earned a reputation
as a champion
for conservative causes, leading
the fight

41:02.660 --> 41:04.495 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to defund Planned Parenthood.

41:04.529 --> 41:06.297 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

41:06.331 --> 41:08.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE PENCE: Millions of pro-life
Americans
shouldn't be asked to fund the
leading abortion

41:08.800 --> 41:10.568 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
provider in the United States.

41:10.601 --> 41:15.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But he didn't
always fall in
line with the Republican Party's
leadership,

41:15.406 --> 41:21.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fighting against President
Bush's signature
education program and expansion
of Medicaid.

41:21.346 --> 41:22.513 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

41:22.547 --> 41:25.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE PENCE: I rise on behalf of
the fringe
in America.

41:25.817 --> 41:33.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As Pence built
his Washington
resume, Kaine was launching
himself into Virginia

41:33.725 --> 41:35.526 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
politics.

41:35.560 --> 41:39.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First serving on city council,
Kaine went
on to become the first white
mayor of Richmond,

41:40.031 --> 41:42.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a majority-black city, in nearly
a decade.

41:42.900 --> 41:48.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SCHAPIRO: His relationship
with African-Americans
has been enduring.

41:48.639 --> 41:53.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it manifests itself not just
in politics,
but in faith.

41:53.177 --> 41:58.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He and Anne Holton attend a
majority-black
African-American Roman Catholic
parish.

41:58.249 --> 42:03.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He went on to
serve as lieutenant
governor under then governor and
now fellow

42:03.654 --> 42:08.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Senator Mark Warner, and was
next elected
governor himself.

42:08.726 --> 42:15.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For Kaine, the 2008 financial
collapse and
the nation's worst mass
shooting, 32 dead

42:15.900 --> 42:19.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at Virginia Tech University,
would consume
his attention.

42:19.437 --> 42:21.305 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

42:21.339 --> 42:25.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM KAINE: As you wrestle with
your sadness,
as you wrestle with your own
feelings of anger

42:25.543 --> 42:32.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or confusion, as you wrestle
with the despair,
do not let hold of that spirit
of the community

42:32.550 --> 42:35.753 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that makes Virginia Tech such a
special place.

42:35.787 --> 42:37.522 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do not lose hold of that.

42:37.555 --> 42:42.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Although Governor
Kaine was
unable to convince a Republican
legislature

42:42.126 --> 42:47.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to adopt stricter background
checks following
the shooting, he did close a
loophole that

42:47.965 --> 42:50.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had permitted the mentally ill
to purchase
guns.

42:50.635 --> 42:52.503 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

42:52.537 --> 42:56.407 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM KAINE: I have always
believed that, however
you serve, what matters is
whether you actually

42:56.441 --> 42:58.509 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
deliver results for people.

42:58.543 --> 43:03.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Schapiro says
these experiences
helped Kaine hone his political
skills.

43:03.848 --> 43:05.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFF SCHAPIRO: He can be very
calculated.

43:05.716 --> 43:07.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He can be very cagey.

43:07.585 --> 43:09.487 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has an acute sense of the
jugular.

43:09.520 --> 43:13.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Kaine's political
star continued
to rise.

43:13.391 --> 43:20.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He helped Barack Obama win
Virginia in 2008,
was named national party chair
the next year,

43:20.231 --> 43:25.169 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and in 2012 ran for the Senate,
and won easily.

43:25.203 --> 43:31.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As Kaine entered Congress, Mike
Pence gave
up his House seat to run for
governor of Indiana.

43:31.876 --> 43:34.812 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
His tenure has been rocky at
times.

43:34.846 --> 43:41.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 2015, Pence signed and
defended a controversial
law that critics charged would
let businesses

43:41.853 --> 43:43.888 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
discriminate against gays and
lesbians.

43:43.921 --> 43:48.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN GROPPE: The business
community in
Indiana really rose up against
it.

43:48.392 --> 43:51.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then, when he agreed to make
changes to
the law, that satisfied neither
side.

43:52.029 --> 43:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The conservatives thought he had
capitulated
and the other side thought that
the changes

43:55.800 --> 43:57.568 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
didn't go far enough.

43:57.602 --> 44:01.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Pence did earn
praise from
conservatives for implementing
significant

44:01.873 --> 44:06.477 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tax cuts and signing a stricter
state abortion
law.

44:06.511 --> 44:11.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump tapped Pence to be
his running
mate just as he was mounting a
tough reelection

44:11.916 --> 44:13.751 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
bid in Indiana.

44:13.784 --> 44:20.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Groppe says Pence is motivated
by aspirations
for higher office, but also by
his Christian

44:20.091 --> 44:21.893 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
faith.

44:21.926 --> 44:25.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN GROPPE: It's a central
part of his
life, and I think he also sees
it as a reason

44:25.863 --> 44:29.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
why -- connected to what he's
doing in public
office.

44:30.001 --> 44:32.503 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said he sees public service
as a calling.

44:32.537 --> 44:34.038 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

44:34.071 --> 44:36.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE PENCE: I'm a Christian, a
conservative
and a Republican, in that order.

44:36.440 --> 44:38.242 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

44:38.276 --> 44:43.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In a similar
vein, Schapiro
says Kaine is driven by a belief
that politics

44:43.214 --> 44:44.949 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
can be faith in action.

44:44.982 --> 44:51.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SCHAPIRO: Faith becomes
sort of the broad
umbrella under which Kaine
operates.

44:51.856 --> 44:55.192 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know that it's the only
thing.

44:55.226 --> 45:02.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is politics and government
as opportunities
for change, as instruments for
good.

45:02.934 --> 45:05.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is what interests and
motivates Kaine.

45:05.570 --> 45:09.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, as we look
forward to
tomorrow night's vice
presidential debate,

45:09.807 --> 45:15.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
